Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Leben und Lehre Christi Rubens Neues Testament"

- Notes about some paintings in Antwerp
- Correspondence with Hans Jürgen Imiela dated 1968
- Photocopies of reproductions of 'Christ giving the keys to saint Peter' and 'Resurrection of Lazarus'
- Reproductions of the 'Baptism of Christ', 'The Miraculous catch of fish', 'Christ and the Woman Taken in Adultery', 'Resurrection'
- Bibliographic references
- Folder addressed to "Professor Dr. Evers Darmstadt - Traisa Waldstr. 43", with correspondence with Helma Schefer dated 1959-61
- Article about 'The Tribute Money' in "Schwäbische Post" dated 20.04.1957
- Extracts from different publications
